&lt;div class="post-text" itemprop="text"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The best solution is to store the mime-type in the DB at the same time you're inserting the image into the blob field. Otherwise you're going to have to the following EACH TIME the image is retrieved:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;$image = $row['imageblob'];  // $row = result row from DB query.

$finfo = new finfo(FILEINFO_MIME);
$mime_type = $finfo-&amp;gt;buffer($image);
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This gets to be expensive very quickly on a busy system, so best do the determination ONCE and then store that result.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Relevant &lt;a href="http://php.net/manual/en/function.finfo-buffer.php"&gt;PHP docs here&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class="post-text" itemprop="text"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You can do something like this 
&lt;code&gt;mixedArray := []interface{}{"astring", 10, &amp;amp;Object{'hello'}}&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Most likely the values that you want to hold share some behavior, in that case what you should really do is create an interface and simply make the array content type that interface.&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class="post-text" itemprop="text"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Return the string from &lt;code&gt;askstuff&lt;/code&gt; and use as needed in the caller:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;func askstuff() string {
    fmt.Println("Input to exit digit X:")
    var input string
    fmt.Scanln(&amp;amp;input)
    return input
}

func main() {
    x := askstuff()
    fmt.Println(x)
}
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
