&lt;div class="post-text" itemprop="text"&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It simply means it contains 4 empty node pointer slices, which is the expected behavior from your code.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It is a slice of slices of node pointers.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Here is a simple modification of your code to show you how it works if you add nodes to your slices:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;package main

import "fmt"

type node struct {
    id int
}

func main() {
    var routingTable [][]*node
    for i := 0; i &amp;lt; 4; i++ {
        routingTable = append(routingTable, []*node{&amp;amp;node{id: i}})
    }
    fmt.Print(routingTable)
}
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Will output the slice of slices of node pointers, containing one node each with a different address:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;[[0x10414020] [0x10414024] [0x10414028] [0x1041402c]]
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Try it yourself &lt;a href="https://play.golang.org/p/Ly-D-4skozr" rel="nofollow noreferrer"&gt;here&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
    &lt;/div&gt;

